  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32agent",
        "args": "Send the line 'ping' over the VCP and read the reply."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 vcp send \"ping\"",
        "description": "Send 'ping' over VCP and collect reply"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "This is a clean VCP-002 send-and-receive. Running it now:\n**COM9 is locked by another application.** The substrate returned `VCPPortInUse` \u2014 something else (PuTTY, Tera Term, CubeIDE console, minicom, etc.) has COM9 open.\n\n**To fix:**\n1. Close whichever serial terminal / IDE console is holding COM9.\n2. Re-run \u2014 the substrate will reopen the port automatically (SB-001 auto-attach).\n\nOnce COM9 is free, the command to re-issue is:\n```\nstm32 vcp send \"ping\"\n```"
}